Absolutely LOVE World of Beer! Excellent servers and management. Food is always fresh and delicious, and you cannot beat their Happy Hour and weekend Brunch. It is always a great time with a relaxed atmosphere.

Rockville Town Center has their own "tap room" with dining, mixed drinks, & a world - of - beer!  About 30 taps complement a wide selection of bottles spanning the globe. An offering sure to please your most discerning beer lover.  This galley-style pub has high ceilings, a generous amount of outside dining, & a nearby garage for cheap parking on evenings & weekends.  Standard pub fare & standard service.  Happy hour has a few $5 apps and a couple of discounted beers. Some daily specials.  May 2021 is their 5 year anniversary, so look out for some events & some bargains.

Stopped in here while waiting for a family member to finish up an appointment. I was excited about the "world" of beers. Ordered a flight and wings. The wings were great; full of flavor, sizable wings, value for money. The choice of beers was not fantastic. Yes, there were several different beers on the menu, but none that were fantastic. I didn't see one that I wanted to have a full pint (or two). NFL Sunday games were on the screens. It was nice to see all the games. The bar set-up is a little tight to the screens though, so you have to crank you neck pretty sharply to watch the games immediately in front of you. The bar service was the down point for me. To the servers credit, it was the first time I was in WOB. They do have quite a selection and I was unprepared to order. That said however, I had to ask for a glass of water twice. I also had to ask for my check twice, ultimately opting for walking to one of the cash registers and waiting there to pay my bill. At one point, the bartender was doing a crossword puzzle that belonged to one of the customers. I stopped counting after she was heads down in the puzzle for more than 2 minutes. Now, you may say 2 minutes is not a long time but pause right now for 120 seconds, think about how you would feel if you were trying to get the bartender's attention for that period of time. Think about the other customers that are also trying to get her attention and now looking at you, shrugging their shoulders with their hands up. I won't be going back.
